<item>
            <title>[LU-9284] striped directory should be able to be accessed even if one stripe MDT is failed.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9284</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In current striped directory implementation, if one stripe MDT failed, the striped directory will not be able to access, which seems unacceptable. So in this case&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. lfs getdirstripe should indicate which stripe is failed.&lt;br/&gt;
2. the left stripes should be able to be accessed, and can be migrated to a new directory.&lt;br/&gt;
3. creating the file/dir on the failed stripe should fail, though it should succeed on other stripes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other suggestions? If some else already create the ticket, please close this one. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
